The paper presents a system that uses artificial intelligence to automatically discover critical mechanics in video games. This involves parsing game descriptions and playtrace information, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The system is also validated through a user study, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of MCTS agents, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SD).
